System Requirements for the use of Word Viewer
 -  A personal computer with an 80386 or higher microprocessor
 -  4 MB of memory (6 MB recommended)
 -  3 MB of hard disk space (6MB free for installation only)
 -  MS-DOS(R) operating system version 3.0 or later
 -  Microsoft Windows (TM) operating system version 3.1 or later
 -  Microsoft Mouse or compatible pointing device

To install Word Viewer, please follow these instructions:

1.	Installation of Word Viewer is designed to take place from within 
	Microsoft Windows.  If Windows is not running, please start it before 
	continuing.

2.	Make sure to close all applications first, and make sure you are not 
	running any utilities or virus protection before proceeding.  

3.	Start File Manager.  From Program Manager, this can be done by 
	double-clicking on the File Manager icon or by choosing Run from the 
	File menu and typing "winfile.exe" in the dialog box.  

4.	Create a new directory for Word Viewer:  a) Choose File Create 
	Directory, b) Type in a name (Ex:  "c:\wordview" ), c) Click OK.  
	Move the WV.EXE file from your download directory into the directory 
	you just created; Word Viewer will install into that directory.  Run 
	the WV.EXE program by double-clicking on it in File Manager or by 
	choosing File Run and typing "wv.exe".

5.	If you are installing off a floppy disk, you can either copy the 
	WV.EXE program onto your hard disk first, or you can run directly off 
	the floppy.  Select the directory you wish to install into in File 
	Manager and choose File Run, "a:wv.exe".

6.	Word Viewer will then automatically expand its files.  These are the 
	correct file sizes and locations:

	File Name	File Size	Location
	===================================================
	vshare.386	   14,933 	\windows\system
	license.doc	   14,336	Word Viewer directory
	readme.doc	   33,792	Word Viewer directory
	sdv.dll	  	  103,904 	Word Viewer directory
	ttembedv.dll	  105,472 	Word Viewer directory
	ttembext.dll	    5,280 	Word Viewer directory
	wordview.exe	1,815,040	Word Viewer directory
	wrdview6.reg	      504 	Word Viewer directory
	wwintlv.dll	  369,152	Word Viewer directory


7.	To run Word Viewer:  double-click on the WORDVIEW.EXE file in File
	Manager.


========================================================================
Installing OLE 2.02:
====================
Word Viewer requires OLE 2.01 or greater.  If the WV.EXE installation
program does not find this on your system, it will halt installation.
You must then install OLE before running WV.EXE again.  You can obtain
OLE 2.02 from any of the sources described below.  If you ordered Word
Viewer directly from Microsoft Sales, Disk #2 contains all the required
files, and you follow the instructions on the disk label.

Note:  If you install Word Viewer, but when you try to run it, you receive
the following error message: "There is not enough memory to start Word
Viewer", then you are probably running OLE 2.0.  Follow these instructions
to install OLE 2.02, and Word Viewer should then load correctly.


WW1116: OLE Version 2.02                                      [win3x]
ID: Q123087    CREATED: 21-NOV-1994   MODIFIED: 29-NOV-1994
.
.
